==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interlope
<hw>In`ter*lope"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Interloped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Interloping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[See
<er>Interloper</er>.]</ety> <def>To run between parties and intercept
without right the advantage that one should gain from the other; to
traffic without a proper license; to intrude; to forestall others; to
intermeddle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interloper</ent>⟦br⟧
